<h3><a href="/news/4210/halo-5-announced">Halo 5 Announced</a></h3>
<span class="author">By Jeff Buckland, 5/16/2014 5:45 AM</span><br/><br/>
<p>343 Industries' general manager Bonnie Ross has <a href="http://news.xbox.com/2014/05/games-halo-journey-announcement">announced</a> <b>Halo 5: Guardians</b>, which will be coming to the Xbox One this fall.  More info will be at E3 next month, but for now, I'm excited to hear that it'll be only a year between the launch of the XB1 and a new <b>Halo</b> game.  In the past I've gone in-depth as to why these console manufacturers don't launch a console with a huge flagship game immediately, so one year is a welcome change from when the Xbox 360 launched and we got a new <b>Halo</b> <i>two years</i> later.<br/><br/>
